=== LibreFactory ===

LibreFactory is an open-source implementation of Factorio[1] written in C++, 
which is also targeting very... low powered hardware. That hardware being from
Windows XP. My personal test rig is running Windows XP Home (x86) SP3 on an
Intel Pentium 4 and a mere 512M of usable RAM. For the GPU, I scored an ATI
Radeon 9000 for cheap, as the built-in GPU has long since died on me.

This project is primarily targeting Windows XP, though I'll do my best to try
and target newer systems on a best effort basis. But for the most part, this is
simply a fun Windows project that I've decided to make open source.

This project is licensed under BSD-4-Clause. It's a straight forward license
that covers everything a license needs to. Lua is included as well scripting is
very important, and it's under the generally very permissive MIT license.

[1] https://factorio.com/

=== How do I build this? ===

With the soon-to-be-implemented build script, '' build.cmd '' ! This handy lil
piece of tooling completely negates the need for a build system, it IS the
build system. The build script also takes in arguments, to run it, you'll need
to use the Developer Command Prompt that comes installed with Visual Studio.

If compiling for non-Windows targets, please use the '' C++03 '' standard!

If/when compiling for non-Windows targets (Linux, OSX, BSD), we recommend that
you use LLVM/clang based compilers. GCC is completely fine, this is just a
suggestion!

=== What about Lua? ===

Lua[1] is an embedded scripting language built in C and used in this project
under the MIT license. Lua is also the same scripting language used in Factorio.

Most of this engine is exposed through Lua, and a "base" Lua module for this
project will also be worked on once there's an engine to expose. Mods and Lua
scripts that are built for Factorio will NOT work here, because the APIs that
are exposed are completely different even at a basic level.

Documentation will be provided as time goes on, keep an eye our for a "docs"
folder!

[1] https://lua.org/about.html
